Pender Build Tools

Run from the tools directory of the repository

Usage:
    -h --help    : print this message, all other command line arguments are ignored
    -l --library : create Pender Library project
    -c --client  : create a Pender Client project, creates a pender library project if one has not already been created or referenced
    -s --libloc  : specify the path of an existing Pender Lib project

Pender Build Tools will generate sane default arguments for the android tool, specify them if you wish to override

Arguments to the Android SDK android tool:
    -n --name     : Project name [default: PenderClient/PenderLib]
    -t --target   : Target ID of the new project [default: will attempt to detect and use the latest version of the sdk]
    -p --path     : The new project's directory [default: current directory]
    -k --package  : Android package name for the application. [default: com.pender]
    -a --activity : Name of the default Activity that is created. [default: PenderActivity]
